"The Marriage of Figaro (Overture)", a free-use public domain song by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, courtesy of Musopen: https://musopen.org/

entries.description:
"Vltava (The Moldau), from Ma vlast (My Homeland)", a free-use public domain song by Bedřich Smetana, courtesy of Musopen: https://musopen.org/

A set of six symphonic poems composed by Smetana, later presented as a single work in 1882 in Prague. The author combined the ideals of nationalistic music with the Symphonic Poem form coined by Listz. Each poem of Má vlast depicts an aspect of the culture of Bohemia. The piece also happens to contain his most famous tune, an adaptation of La Mantovana, a song attributed to tenor Giuseppe Cenci - and also the basis for the Israeli national anthem.
